source to generate images with responsive breakpoints https://www.responsivebreakpoints.com/
	sizes
	srcset


TASGS
	meta tag:
		- viewport: * when we use the width=device-width, force the browser to adopt their
			real viewport width in the mobiles devices
			* when use initial-scale=1, say to the browser that the relationship between css pixel and 
			devices-independet pixel (dpi) are 1:1
			<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, viewport-fit=cover">

CSS
	box-sizing: border-box; - padding and border are included in the width and height:
	background-position: sets the starting position of a background image.


MEDIA QUERY
	only: The only keyword prevents older browsers that do not support media queries with media features 
		from applying the specified styles. It has no effect on modern browsers.